# Commit Message Rules

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

## Types

- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation
- `style`: Formatting, whitespace
- `refactor`: Code restructuring
- `perf`: Performance improvement
- `test`: Tests
- `build`: Build system
- `ci`: CI configuration
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks
- `revert`: Revert previous commit

## Scope (Optional)

Common scopes: `app`, `components`, `styles`, `config`, `deps`

## Guidelines

- Subject: imperative mood, lowercase, 50-72 characters, no period
- Body: imperative mood, max 72 characters per line, explain "what" and "why" (not "how")
- Footer: `BREAKING CHANGE: <description>`
- Initial commits: Can be longer since they set up the whole project

## Examples

```
feat(auth): add user login
fix(components): resolve button click handler
docs: update README
refactor(app): simplify layout structure
```
